/-!
# Paper: Quark Confinement and the Matter-Sector Mass-Gap Floor on the Recognition Lattice

Self-contained Lean 4 proof companion for the paper
"Quark Confinement and the Matter-Sector Mass-Gap Floor from Recognition
Science: A Machine-Verified Discrete-Lattice Derivation"
(Washburn, April 2026).

This module is intentionally self-contained: it depends only on
`RecognitionScience.Constants`, `RecognitionScience.Cost`, and
`RecognitionScience.Foundation.QuarkColors`, all of which are already
in the public Recognition Science framework that includes the
T0--T8 forcing chain.

## Two coupled theorems

1. **Confinement from ledger topology** (Section 5 of the paper).
   The J-cost of separating a non-singlet color excitation by `r`
   φ-rungs on the recognition lattice is `J(φ^r)`, which is zero at
   `r = 0`, strictly positive at every `r ≥ 1`, strictly monotone in
   `r`, and divergent as `r → ∞`. The color singlet is the unique
   strict cost minimizer; isolated quarks are not in the spectrum.

2. **Matter-sector mass-gap floor** (Section 6 of the paper).
   The first-rung holonomy phase of the recognition connection
   equals `J(φ) = φ - 3/2`. The matter-sector mass-squared floor
   above the canonical vacuum is `m_gap² = J(φ) · ℏ_R`, which sits
   below both `M_W²` and `M_Z²` in canonical units.

## Master certificates

The paper packages two certificates: `QCDConfinementFromLedgerCert`
(eight clauses) and `YangMillsMassGapCert` (eight clauses). Both
are inhabited (`qcdConfinementFromLedgerCert` and
`yangMillsMassGapCert`).

## Status

Zero `sorry`, zero RS-internal axioms. Compiles against the public
framework's lean-toolchain (currently `leanprover/lean4:v4.27.0-rc1`).

The companion paper text and PDF are maintained separately. The Lean
proofs here are the formal substrate; the paper carries the prose
derivation in full.

## Build instructions

```bash
lake exe cache get          -- one-time Mathlib cache (~2 GB)
lake build RecognitionScience.Papers.YangMillsMassGap
```

The transitive dependency closure for this module is small: only
`Constants`, `Cost`, and `Foundation.QuarkColors` (with
`PhiForcing`, `PhiForcingDerived`, `DimensionForcing`,
`ParticleGenerations`, `LawOfExistence`, `DiscretenessForcing`
pulled in transitively). A clean cold build takes about a minute
on top of the Mathlib cache.

